The '''flameback angelfish''' or '''flameback pygmy angelfish''' (''Centropyge aurantonotus'') is an [[omnivorous]] [[marine angelfish]], with blue body and yellow to orange colouration from the face to middle or end of dorsal fin. It is easily confused with the [[orangeback angelfish]] (''Centropyge acanthops''), but in the latter the yellow to orange colouration extends to cover the entire back.
It is native to the southern [[Caribbean Sea]] and the coastal waters of [[Brazil]]; it reaches a maximum length of {{convert|8|cm|in}}.

When kept in an [[aquarium]] flameback angelfish are distributed throughout the tank. They prefer [[reef]] tanks to fish only tanks.

